M|Cros|tx|`rc.cache()` only works within one request. For data shared across sequential requests (us clicks button A then button B), use an LRU cache.
M|Cros|**Im|**
M|Cros|tx|```ts
M|Cros|tx|import { LRUCache } from 'lru-cache'
M|Cros|tx|const cache = new LRUCache<string, any>({
M|Cros|max|1000,
M|Cros|ttl|5 * 60 * 1000  // 5 minutes
M|Cros|tx|})
M|Cros|expo|string) {
M|Cros|tx|const cached = cache.get(id)
M|Cros|tx|if (cached) return cached
M|Cros|cons|{ id } })
M|Cros|tx|cache.set(id, us)
M|Cros|tx|return us
M|Cros|tx|}
M|Cros|// R|DB query, result cached
M|Cros|// R|cache hit, no DB query
M|Cros|tx|```
M|Cros|tx|Use when sequential us actions hit multiple endpoints needing the same data within seconds.
M|Cros|**Wi|//vc.com/doc/fluid-compute):** LRU caching is esp effective bc multiple concurrent requests can share the same fn instance and cache. This means the cache persists across requests w/o needing external storage like Redis.
M|Cros|**In|** Each invocation runs in isolation, so consider Redis for cross-process caching.
M|Cros|Refe|[https://github.com/isaacs/node-lru-cache](https://github.com/isaacs/node-lru-cache)